user.about:
Greetings fellow Jedi!

My name is Marini...

Star Wars and Harry Potter nerd, a property developer, part-time property sales executive, and a passionate latin dancer!

Food & dessert lover, who loves going to Victorian country side to harvest my own honey.. 

Most of my travels have been done either solo or with my best travel buddy (my super-cool-a-little-shopaholic Mama!). I love going to historic places, learning different cultures, visiting museums and admiring the architecture of different countries. 

My favourite travel destinations so far are Japan and New York... and Europe!!! 
I recently just visited Europe with my Mama. We went to Milan, Lake Como, Turino, Geneva, Montreux, and Paris... my my my I knew Europe was pretty...but I was NOT expecting to fall head over heel with her!  And the soaps they have there.... heavenly!

Our next trip is to visit Prague and Stockholm... I'm beyooonnddddd excitedddd!!!!

My style of travelling is definitely NOT to pack light. We have a big family and we can't leave anyone behind when it comes to gifts! I remember coming back from New York with my Mama with 12 suitcases.. all filled with gifts for our friends and family...LOL! Below is a very common conversation between myself and either the hotel concierge, or the taxi driver:

Concierge/Driver: "Are you travelling with your family, Miss?"
Me: "Yes I am actually...*sheepishly* a family of 2"  
Concierge/Driver: "WHHHATTTTTTT"

HAHAHHHAH!! Yup! Every. Single. Time.

Anyways, my passion in life is to build relationships with the people around me. I love reading other people's success stories, and it makes me sooo happy when I see the people around me succeed in life. I strongly believe that when you share more in life, and the more you help others, the more generous life will be towards you... and I feel this in my life daily.

Soooo.... lately I have been a little bit curious with DIY home projects... making truffle honey, homemade artisan soaps, and natural beauty products... So you might just get lucky and randomly get some home-made stuff from me when you book my place! LOL!

hosts.about:
Roomerang is an end-to-end short stays team based in Melbourne.

We are avid travellers and know how hard it can be to find comfortable and cosy, yet affordable accommodation. We try to remove all the complications surrounding your stay, so you can focus on other important aspects of your trip. And if you feel we have left anything out, let us know and we would love to help.

Roomerang provides professionally cleaned and well-kept, affordable stays presenting you with a home to return to no matter who you are, where you're from or what you are here for!

co_host.description:
Welcome to The Wizarding Room of Melbourne, where Wizards and Witches of all ages are welcomed...

A true fan’s home, secretly located north of the big city of Melbourne, all visitors must swear an unbreakable vow to keep the location from being discovered by Muggles!

In this room, you may choose to sleep aboard the Train Cabin or in the Magical School Dorm, take mugshots like a Wanted Prisoner, and try on a Broomstick! 
BYO Buttahbeer, and access the Department of Magic!

Have Fun!

2 Bedrooms, 3 SofaBeds, 2 Bathroom, 1 Carpark

Sleeps Maximum 4 adults & 3 little ones

Don’t have an AirBnB account? Use this link to receive a credit off your first stay: www.airbnb.com.au/r/marinit1

Welcome to the Wizarding Room of Melbourne...featuring original, vintage and new memorabilia inspired by our most favourite magical childhood novels. This brand new, spacious and modern apartment is conveniently located in North Melbourne, approximately 5 minutes from Melbourne CBD. 

DISCLAIMER:
Please note that The Wizarding Room of Melbourne is not endorsed by and have no association or affiliation with the Harry Potter & the Cursed Child play, the Harry Potter novels, movies and related intellectual property or their respective rights holders. All items in the Wizarding Room of Melbourne are personal collection and home decor of the Host. 

FREE PARKING on the premise is available throughout your stay (1 car).


LIVING ROOM

- Spacious and modern with pull out 3-seater sofa bed that sleeps 2 people.

- Super fast unlimited NBN Wi-Fi for minimal to no buffering time during Netflix!

- 55” Smart HDTV with Netflix enabled, so you can stream all the latest movies and re-watch all the Harry Potter sequels.

- North facing window allowing ample of natural light into the apartment

- Block out blinds so you can sleep in til late even on the sofa bed.

- Spacious working space for business travellers.

- Quiet & Cozy fun balcony

- Board Games for family fun time

- AND many many more amazing magical items that will bring back so much happy memory from your childhood..



KITCHEN
-A pantry fully stocked with a range of tea & coffee to help you start your day. 

-French Press Coffee/Tea maker, Toaster & Electric Kettles

-Fully equipped kitchen, including pots & pans, tumblers, mugs, and dining set.




BEDROOMS
- Posture-pedic queen size mattress with 2 different themes

- Block out blinds to prevent sun glare from waking you up too early

- Massive wardrobe to fit all your clothes and costumes!


BATHROOMS
- Rainmaker head shower & detachable hand-held shower, with complimentary body wash, shampoo, conditioner, and liquid hand soap.

- Nice fluffy towels and hair dryer to help you care for your witch’s mane..



LAUNDRY
- Washing Machine & Dryer so you'll never run out of clean robes

- laundry liquid/powder, or BYO preferred.

- Iron & Ironing board, don't step out in a creased robe!

The whole Wizarding Room / Apartment is yours to enjoy on your own with complete privacy. We offer a simple check-in process so that you can arrive any time after the official check-in time of 3PM. 

The apartment building has a common shared rooftop herb garden which guests can access.

Please do inform us of the number of guests upon booking, and if you will require extra blankets.

BEFORE ARRIVAL:
We will send you all the information that you will need to ensure a smooth arrival and check-in process. 
- Our Key Ninja Team will contact you prior to your arrival to organise a key delivery. 

Please do not hesitate to ask us any question you have. 

AFTER ARRIVAL:
 We will usually message our guests after arrival to check if they needed anything, and we are always more than happy to provide recommendations. 

MEETING WITH HOST:
As I am working full time and travelling for work a lot, I do not usually meet my guests. 
But when I am in Melbourne, we might bump into each other in the lift... If you recognise me, please say hi!! I won't cast a spell on you.

ISSUES:
If a problem arise, please contact me via AirBnB. My co-host and I are very fast in responding, and we will always try to resolve any issue as soon as possible.

Get the perfect mix of quiet residential life and the convenience of city life when you stay here. North Melbourne has breakfast cafes and boutique shops to enjoy close by, or drive just five minutes to the heart of the Central Business District.

- The apartment is 20mins taxi/uber ride from the Melbourne Airport. 

- Or you can take the Skybus to Southern Cross Station, and catch an uber to the apartment (Uber will cost around $6)

- Nearest tram stop is only 1 block away. Catch tram no. 57 from Errol St or Victoria St to go to the city. 

- Or you can enjoy a short 5-10 minute walk to Elizabeth St.

- Queen Victoria Market is only 5-10 minutes away by foot, where you can find lots of fun shopping and eateries...

- Visit the nearby Lygon St for an authentic Italian dining experience...

- FREE PARKING is available throughout your stay for 1 car. Affordable street-parking available in front of the apartment building.

DISCOUNTS:
Please note we do not offer additional discounts above those already provided for weekly stays. 
Our Wizarding Room is competitively priced, and we take pride into offering an excellent, fun and unique experience to all our guests. We are not merely offering a clean place to sleep.


A FEW RULES:

- MEDIA: While all guests are allowed to take photos and videos to post on social media regarding your stay in the apartment, we do not allow - Any commercial event / interview with any entity or party to take place in the premise. - No commercial video making is to take place without the approval or explicit consent from us.

- NO SHOES in the apartment/bedroom. Please take your shoes off at the entrance, and place them on the tiled area near the entrance. 

- All props in the glass cabinet are meant to be locked in. Please do not try to access them. 

- DO NOT MOVE or SWING on Dementor-looking creature. Or it will give you a kiss..

- Do NOT touch the LEGOs and puzzles

- Whilst I encourage you to have fun with the board games, wands and brooms provided, please be mindful of the neighbours and keep the noise to a minimum level after hours. 

- Do not take any prop out of the apartment. 

- Whilst the apartment is children friendly, please do ask your children to be gentle with the toys. 

- Please immediately inform us if any damage occurred. Excessive cleaning and/or any damage to items in the apartment will result in payment request to guests. 

- STRICTLY NO PARTIES!

All my memorabilia are very precious to me and sourced either during my holidays in the USA, and are part of my personal collection. Please do treat them with care like you would your own. Any breakage will result in bond deduction or more.
co_host.directions:
Meet-up Key Delivery

Our Key Ninja will call you prior to arrival to organise a suitable time for key delivery.

Upon check out they will also call you to organise a key pick up.

Your apartment is located in the back building. When you enter the apartment from the street, go pass the first corridor, out the first building and across the courtyard. You will need to swipe your key again to enter the second building. 

CARPARK ACCESS
The apartment comes with a FREE secure carpark within the premise. 
Carpark entrance is located to the left of the building (when you're standing facing the building). 
Once you have obtained your keys, drive your car to the carpark entrance, and use the black carpark remote to open the gate (press button 1). The gate will automatically close behind you. 
Park in the space marked as "B1-23”

There are also ample of on-street parking space in the area. 

The closest tram stop is on Errol St, with tram 57 taking you to the CBD via Victoria St, Elizabeth St, and Queen Victoria Market.
